It occurs to me that if a small group of players are going to be proposing
stuff regularly, (as has been the case, with Gen Chaos, Kolja and I) then
the Duty to Vote rule is going to cycle through the list of Players much
faster than was originally expected. 

In fact, it's a bit of a bug that the frequency that a player is Required
to Serve is not just a function of the number of players, but also of the
activity of the other players. The more active the other players are, the
more often an inactive player will have to propose. 

I suggest a modification: There are three statuses, for the time being I'll
call them -1, 0 and +1. -1 corresponds to being Required to Serve, 0 
corresponds to not required to serve, +1 means that you have a credit.
We continue with the rotating list, so that each week two (or maybe just
one) Players at the top of the list have their status decreased by one 
(-1 stays where it is), and are moved to the end of the list. When a 
player makes a proposal, eir status is increased by one (max +1) but e
does not move in the list.

Players whose Status is negative for two weeks continuously are guilty
of Failure to Propose, and their status is set to zero.

That way, active players who propose often will still have their turn
at the top of the list, but they won't have to do anything, because they
already have a "proposal credit".

I'll see if I can formalise this as a proto soon.

