I've noticed that in the last two batches I've cast the same number of votes 
FOR as AGAINST.  I wonder what kind of strategies would result if players 
were required to do so?  Or even mildly encouraged?  Something like the
following might be interesting, once voting costs something again... 

Protoproposal
'Balanced' voting

Amend the second paragraph of Rule 1442 to read:

      As soon as possible after the end of the Voting Period of a
      given batch of Proposals, the Assessor shall bill each Voting Entity a
      number of Voting Tokens equal to the voting cost for
      that batch multiplied by the absolute value of the
      difference between the number of votes FOR cast by that entity 
      on Proposals in that batch and the number of votes AGAINST cast 
